MBBS in Philippines is one of the best destinations to study a course of medicine for Indian students. It enables the students to have brighter career growth after Study MBBS in Philippines.

More than 8000 foreign students are taking admission to study MBBS in Philippines every year. The MBBS course from Philippines is globally recognized including the Medical Council of India. The best part is that almost everyone speaks English in the Philippines which is an added advantage to students who want to fulfill their dream to pursue MBBS in Philippines.

{/* */}

Why MBBS in Philippines?

Most Indian students wish to pursue MBBS abroad but a few students can fulfill their dream into reality. The Philippines offers a golden opportunity to these students to attain their aim. The Indian students can choose to study MBBS in Philippines because of the following reasons:

  • Travel to the Philippines is much easier and even economical than traveling to other countries.
  • A medical program provided by the MCI approved medical colleges in Philippines to their students is recognized worldwide.
  • English is spoken in the Philippines so there would not be any problem while interacting with others. The language of coaching is also English.
  • MCI (Medical Council of India) approves medical colleges as well as universities and follows the US education system.
  • The students who have cleared MBBS in Philippines can also practice in India.
  • A unified problem-based learning approach offers better exposure to future medical practitioners.
  • MCI approved medical colleges in Philippines have advanced teaching techniques with outstanding facilities equipped with the well-established infrastructure and utilizes up-to-date machinery in their laboratories
  • MBBS in Philippines for Indian students is beneficial as they can also have the option to start working on preparation for the United States Medical Licensing Examination (USMLE) to study Post Graduate Degrees.
  • The Philippines is extremely safe for Indian students and the environment is also safe.
  • There is no donation or capitation fee required in Philippines medical college.
  • MBBS in Philippines best colleges provides the quality education at affordable fees.
  • The cost of living is quite favorable for Indian students as there are excellent boarding and lodging provided by the university with the availability of Indian food for the students.
  • Study MBBS in Philippines provides the magnificent theoretical as well as practical education which empowers the students to become successful practitioners.

Philippines Medical College Fee Structure for Indian Students

Study MBBS in Philippines is an excellent option for Indian medical students who wish to pursue MBBS. The cost of complete course of MBBS in Philippines is quite reasonable and there is no donation fee in the Philippines Medical Colleges.

Medical Universities/colleges in the Philippines charge low tuition fees as compared to Indian universities/colleges. MBBS in Philippines fees would range anywhere between 12 to 25 lacs Indian Rupees on the basis of the ranking of the Philippines medical college. Medical degree offered by the MBBS universities/colleges in the Philippines is accredited by MCI, WHO.
